 Dutywa - Dutywa police arrested two men, aged 23 and 25, for possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition over the weekend. "Both suspects were arrested on Sunday, at about 19:00, at Nyhwarha Village, Dutywa," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "The 23-year-old suspect was found with unlicensed firearm -  a pistol with 16 rounds of ammunition. "The 25-year-old suspect was found with another unlicensed pistol with five rounds of ammunition." He said that the firearms will be sent for ballistic tests to establish if they were not used in the commission of crime around Dutywa and the surrounding areas. "The two suspects will appear before the Dutywa Magistrate’s Court on Tuesday." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 